image.caption: Black clouds hang over the Bangabandhu national stadium in Dhaka
image.longCaption: Black clouds hang over Banghabandhu nation stadium in Dhaka as the pitch is covered with plastic 20 April 2003. South African and India are to play the final match of the TVS tri-nation cricket tournament, but heavy rain stopped the match before it could start

milestones.description: India's 201-run win against Bangladesh is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 186-run win against Kenya

stories.title: Bangladesh succumb to Yuvraj-inspired India
stories.summary: A superb 102 from Yuvraj Singh - his maiden ODI century - proved an effective catalyst in India's comprehensive 200-run win over Bangladesh, their biggest-ever in one-day cricket

image.caption: Black clouds hang over the Bangabandhu national stadium in Dhaka
